Package frc.robot

Contains Constants, Robot, and RobotContainer. This is where we will put most of the "pieces" of the robot together, from the subsystems to the commands, all into a neat package that can all run at once thanks to the black magic of command-based programming.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Constants
    The Constants class provides a convenient place for teams to hold robot-wide numerical or boolean constants.
    Constants.ClimberConstants
    Contains all the constants for the Climber subsystem.
    Constants.ControllerConstants
    Contains all the constants for the Xbox controller.
    Constants.DriveConstants
    Contains all the constants for the robot drive train.
    Constants.IndexerConstants
    Contains all the constants for the Indexer subsystem.
    Constants.LimelightConstants
    Contains all the constants for the Limelight.
    Constants.PickupConstants
    Contains all the constants for the Pickup subsystem.
    Constants.PivotConstants
    Contains all the constants for the pivot subsystem that raises the pickup.
    Constants.ShooterConstants
    Contains all the constants for the Shooter subsystem.
    Constants.TestConstants
    Despite the name, this contains the constants for the CustomSpeedController class to increment or decrement the speeds on the fly.
    Constants.TrajectoryPathnames
    Contains each of the trajectory pathnames that correspond to each autonomous routine.
    Main
    As noted down below, you do NOT edit this class at all.
    Robot
    The VM is configured to automatically run this class, and to call the functions corresponding to each mode, as described in the TimedRobot documentation.
    RobotContainer
    This class is where the bulk of the robot should be declared.
